snippet.textDisplay: I really don't see the point of vertically folding smartphones. I really like the concept of the Galaxy fold because it's functional when folded, and when you unfold it it becomes a small tablet. But with the z flip, it feels like a normal phone that folds. And even when it's unfolded, it seems way too tall and narrow to be able to do much on it. I would understand if it added extra functionality, but all it adds is a tiny screen and the ability to fit it in pockets easier, which wasn't even a problem in the first place
